    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-14T04:10:56+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-14T04:10:56+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-13T17:40:56Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-13T17:40:56Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure extends from a high south of WA, across waters well south of SA. The high slowly moves eastwards to be centred over the Tasman Sea by Saturday afternoon, with further high pressure systems building well south of the Bight. A trough over inland WA is expected to move across western and northern SA on Sunday and into the new week. A cold front clips the southeast early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-14T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-15T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-13T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-14T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds east to southeasterly 25 to 35 km/h tending east to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the early afternoon then tending east to southeasterly in the late afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures 30 to 37.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:50am to 5:00pm, UV Index predicted to reach 10 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-03-15T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-16T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-14T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-15T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower west of Leigh Creek, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm near the eastern border in the late afternoon and evening. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h turning north to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then tending northeast to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 17 and 27 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to high 30s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-03-16T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-17T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-15T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-16T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. High chance of rain west of Leigh Creek, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm west of Leigh Creek in the evening. Winds northeast to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending north to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h during the morning then tending northeast to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to 22 to 27 with daytime temperatures reaching 27 to 36.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-03-17T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-18T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-16T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-17T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. High chance of showers north of Leigh Creek, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds east to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 18 and 25 with daytime temperatures reaching 24 to 32.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
